---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE } from '../data/site';
---

<Base title="Survival Phase Basics" description="Shift at Midnight survival phase basics — board up, set traps, hide, and communicate when customers turn dangerous.">
  <div class="page-grid">
    <div>

      <!-- Hero -->
      <div class="panel hero" style="padding: 24px 28px;">
        <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot red"></span> Danger Response · {SITE.evidenceVersion}</span>
        <h1>Survival Phase Basics</h1>
        <p class="lead">When official sources describe what happens when customers turn dangerous — board up, set traps, hide, and communicate. Exact trigger conditions and tactics are held until verified.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Trigger boundary -->
      <section class="panel section">
        <h2>Trigger Boundary</h2>
        <p style="margin-top: 4px; font-size: 13px;">Official platform sources describe the survival phase as a consequence of the inspection loop. The exact trigger conditions are not published in the current evidence.</p>

        <div class="hold-panel" style="margin-top: 14px;">
          <h3>🔒 What stays unverified</h3>
          <p>Exact trigger conditions for the survival phase — what specific customer behavior, failed check, or game state activates danger mode. Do not guess. Observe in the demo or wait for official material.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Response board -->
      <section class="panel section">
        <h2>Official Response Options</h2>
        <p style="margin-top: 4px; font-size: 13px;">These four actions are described in official sources as the player's options when the survival phase is active. They are listed here as a planning framework, not as a verified tactics guide.</p>

        <!-- Response cards: 2x2 grid -->
        <div class="response-board" style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr)); gap: 12px; margin-top: 16px;">

          <div class="response-card" style="padding: 16px; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 8px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);">
            <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
              <div style="width: 36px; height: 36px; border-radius: 7px; background: rgba(255, 197, 95, 0.12); border: 1px solid rgba(255, 197, 95, 0.2); display: grid; place-items: center; color: var(--gold);">
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/><line x1="3" y1="9" x2="21" y2="9"/><line x1="9" y1="21" x2="9" y2="9"/></svg>
              </div>
              <h3 style="font-size: 15px;">Board Up</h3>
            </div>
            <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.55;">Seal entry points to slow or stop dangerous customers from reaching you. Whether this is permanent or temporary depends on game state — not yet verified.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="response-card" style="padding: 16px; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 8px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);">
            <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
              <div style="width: 36px; height: 36px; border-radius: 7px; background: rgba(255, 197, 95, 0.12); border: 1px solid rgba(255, 197, 95, 0.2); display: grid; place-items: center; color: var(--gold);">
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polygon points="13 2 3 14 12 14 11 22 21 10 12 10 13 2"/></svg>
              </div>
              <h3 style="font-size: 15px;">Set Traps</h3>
            </div>
            <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.55;">Deploy available tools to gain an advantage or delay threats. Exact trap types, quantities, and placement rules are not confirmed from official sources.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="response-card" style="padding: 16px; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 8px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);">
            <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
              <div style="width: 36px; height: 36px; border-radius: 7px; background: rgba(255, 197, 95, 0.12); border: 1px solid rgba(255, 197, 95, 0.2); display: grid; place-items: center; color: var(--gold);">
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M1 12s4-8 11-8 11 8 11 8-4 8-11 8-11-8-11-8z"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"/></svg>
              </div>
              <h3 style="font-size: 15px;">Hide</h3>
            </div>
            <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.55;">Break line of sight and avoid detection. Official sources confirm hide as a response option. Best hiding spots, duration limits, and visibility rules require hands-on testing.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="response-card" style="padding: 16px; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 8px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);">
            <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
              <div style="width: 36px; height: 36px; border-radius: 7px; background: rgba(255, 197, 95, 0.12); border: 1px solid rgba(255, 197, 95, 0.2); display: grid; place-items: center; color: var(--gold);">
                <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 15a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h14a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z"/></svg>
              </div>
              <h3 style="font-size: 15px;">Communicate</h3>
            </div>
            <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.55;">In co-op, call out your position, what you see, and what you need. Call category (sightings, sounds, locations) not specific answers. Supports team survival.</p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Co-op survival notes -->
      <section class="panel section">
        <h2>Co-op Survival Notes</h2>
        <p style="margin-top: 4px; font-size: 13px;">When playing with 2-3 players, the survival phase adds coordination requirements on top of individual survival.</p>

        <div class="check-list" style="margin-top: 14px;">
          <div class="check-item done">
            <div class="check-num">✓</div>
            <div class="check-text">
              <strong>Call position, not panic</strong>
              <p>Teammates need to know where you are and what you see. Use directional calls: "back room", "counter", "aisle 2" — not emotional callouts.</p>
            </div>
            <span class="check-badge good">Spatial comms</span>
          </div>
          <div class="check-item done">
            <div class="check-num">✓</div>
            <div class="check-text">
              <strong>Assign survival roles early</strong>
              <p>Decide in advance who handles store tasks if one player is hiding or trapped. Avoid both players converging on the same survival action and abandoning the store.</p>
            </div>
            <span class="check-badge good">Role discipline</span>
          </div>
          <div class="check-item partial">
            <div class="check-num">?</div>
            <div class="check-text">
              <strong>Does the store continue running during survival?</strong>
              <p>Whether quota, deliveries, and shelf tasks still apply during an active survival phase is not confirmed. Observe in the demo.</p>
            </div>
            <span class="check-badge warn">Observe</span>
          </div>
          <div class="check-item hold">
            <div class="check-num">✗</div>
            <div class="check-text">
              <strong>Exact enemy routes and behavior patterns</strong>
              <p>How dangerous customers move, patrol, or hunt is not confirmed from official sources. Do not publish as fact.</p>
            </div>
            <span class="check-badge muted">HOLD</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- What is unverified -->
      <section class="panel section">
        <h2>What Stays Unverified</h2>
        <p style="margin-top: 4px; font-size: 13px;">These are the most-asked survival questions that require hands-on testing or official guide material before publishing.</p>

        <div class="can-cannot" style="margin-top: 14px;">
          <div class="cannot-card">
            <h3>✗ Not yet verified</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Exact trigger conditions (customer type, failed check threshold, timing)</li>
              <li>Trap types and item inventory available during survival</li>
              <li>Best hiding spots and line-of-sight rules</li>
              <li>Enemy movement patterns, speed, and detection radius</li>
              <li>Whether hiding breaks if a customer enters your cell</li>
              <li>Survival phase duration or win condition</li>
              <li>How player count affects survival difficulty</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>

    <aside>
      <div class="panel side">
        <h2>Related Pages</h2>
        <div style="display: grid; gap: 8px; margin-top: 12px;">
          <p><a href="/beginner-guide/" style="color: var(--gold);">→ First Shift Guide</a></p>
          <p><a href="/customer-checks/" style="color: var(--gold);">→ Customer Inspection</a></p>
          <p><a href="/co-op/" style="color: var(--gold);">→ Co-op Prep Guide</a></p>
          <p><a href="/demo/" style="color: var(--gold);">→ Demo Guide</a></p>
          <p><a href="/sources/" style="color: var(--gold);">→ Source Matrix</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="panel side" style="margin-top: 14px;">
        <h2>Source Basis</h2>
        <div class="mini">
          <h3>SAM-SRC-001</h3>
          <p>Steam — online co-op detective horror; survival actions described as game features</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mini" style="margin-top: 8px;">
          <h3>SAM-SRC-004</h3>
          <p>Xbox — online co-op / multiplayer confirmed; survival-phase specifics require demo verification</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .response-board { grid-template-columns: 1fr !important; }
  }
</style>
